## Markdown Notes Conventions

### File Naming
- Markdown filenames are always all lowercase (no capitalization)
- Use spaces between words in filenames, not hyphens or underscores

### Formatting
- Never use italics or emphasis (no `*text*` or `_text_`) in any file
- Start research/note files directly with the motivating question — no label or header for it
- When listing book titles, link them to Google Image Search (format: `https://www.google.com/search?tbm=isch&q=Book+Title+Author+textbook`)

### Product Linking
- Any time a product is mentioned in a note, it must have either a purchase page link or a Google Image Search link
- Exception: if the product has its own local page in the note collection, link to that local page instead (the local page will contain the external links)

### Workflow
- Commit after each file change so changes can be reverted if problems are discovered
- Always update the active note with new findings during a research conversation — never ask whether to update it

